nology of Lawrence's career, and the essays cover the full range of his creative achievement, from analyses of major novels and short fiction to reassessments of his poetry and visionary thought. No single ideology or methodology dominates the volume: the contributions include traditional humanistic studies and formalist readings as well as feminist approaches and analyses that reflect current poststructuralist theory. Some of the essays implicitly challenge the validity of others, and some may well cause controversy. Taken together, they illuminate the richness of Lawrence's writings and the multifaceted nature of his accomplishments.D. H. Lawrence; A Centenary Consideration will be rewarding reading both for Lawrencian specialists and for others interested in modem literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aBalbert, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiBattista, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleishman, Avrom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Sandra M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiely, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLitz, A. Walton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcus, Phillip L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcus, Phillip L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerloff, Marjorie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRossman, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpilka, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators